According to SystemVerilog spec, the example code below with typed constructor call (` c = D::new()`) is legal syntax. Which is supported by QuestaSim 2021.2

    class C;
        virtual function void hello();
            $info("Hello from C");
        endfunction // hello
    endclass // C
    
    
    class D extends C;
        virtual function void hello();
            $info("Hello from D");
        endfunction // hello
    endclass // D
    
    
    module tb;
        C c;
        initial begin
            c = D::new();
            c.hello();
        end
    endmodule // tb
